@adomasbaliuka I've added the logic to validate the variant-selector characters here: #16368

Maybe you could have a look, especially at the changes in [`TextBased.lean`](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/16368/files#diff-c973e59ceee698f73d927eed559746d5b761304155603aac9f1f41f7375b7e85) and if you think they are reasonable, I could directly push them to this PR.

In particular it showed me that there is already one place in mathlib where there are characters followed by both selectors `\uFE0E\FE0F`, which is not valid Unicode, so having a linter for this would certainly be good.

@adomasbaliuka What do you think of the version I now pushed? Maybe you can test for speed again. This way should be even less looping and it's overall a bit shorter.

Also, maybe you know better how to write the `parse?_errorContext` entry? I don't fully understand that yet.

Let me know what you think, and if you're happy I could clean up the text and tests and fix the linter warnings

